President Donald Trump attended the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, becoming the second sitting US president to do so. His main message was that a prosperous America benefits the world, and fair economic competition is essential for that prosperity. Trump also highlighted the opportunities for investment in the American economy and emphasized his "America First" vision. The forum provided an opportunity for Trump to build closer ties with US allies and gain global support for American businesses. Other high-profile attendees included French President Emmanuel Macron, German Chancellor Angela Merkel, and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau.